            "answer_text": "Can K-pop trainees interact or befriend K-pop idols?  Today we'll talk about an episode of \u201cIdol School\" wherein Momo and Mina dropped in on some practicing JYPE trainees.  If you watched \u201cSixteen,\u201d you may remember Natty and Jiwon. The trainees were ecstatic to see their unnies. The segment had a lot of catching up, but the older girls also gave advice. At one point, the trainees asked about \u201cOoh Ahh\" choreo.  They were called the \u201cOoh Ahh Team,\u201d so they were doubtlessly practicing for a showcase, much like how the Twice trainees performed lots of Miss A and Wonder Girls stuff for their events.  Like Main Dancers should do, Mina and Momo demonstrate the \u201cU Formation\u201d of their hip roll. And so on. Yes, K-pop trainees are permitted to have relationships with idols. It is obviously encouraged, in fact. But I'm sure you'd have a hard time finding close cross-company connections. Everybody from this episode were JYP employees. However. April Naeun left JYPE for DSP Media as a trainee and Momo said in a VLIVE that she missed her. As Twice School Meal Club still maintain a friendship with Naeun, it makes sense that they stayed in touch after Naeun left, trained with DSP and debuted with April.  Okay bye. ",
