            "answer_text": "*note: I\u2019ve answered a similar question before so I copy/pasted most of the answer Yes and No. There\u2019s 2 types of scenarios in this situation. If, for example, two trainees train together but one of them debuts before the other, then yes in that situation, the Kpop IDOL is friends and close with the other who\u2019s still a trainee. Those two are friends because there was a time where they trained together. But I think most of the time, especially if it\u2019s a larger company with bigger facilities, the trainees would not even see the artists in their company because the artists and trainees have different schedules and/or train in different facilities. I read somewhere once that a senior SM artist (I think Taeyeon) said she didn\u2019t know who all the NCT members are. Or on ProduceX101, when the Starship trainees were about to do their performance, Soyou, who is a Starship artist, stated that that was the first time she\u2019s seen the boys. Plus often times, the Korean sunbae/hoobae culture where you have to look up and respect your seniors or people older than you, often prevents idols and trainees from getting close because the trainees see the idols as their seniors they respect. So the more established the idol is, the less likely you\u2019ll enter the company today and become friends with them while being a trainee. Like you can\u2019t enter JYP as a trainee and expect to see Twice just chilling there regularly and hopefully one day run in to Momo and become BFFs with her. But there are occasions where if the trainees are training and an established idol happens to be walking by, they may stop and give some advice but that\u2019s about as far as interactions between idols and new trainees. It\u2019s not like a trainee entering YG today would leave with a phone full of numbers of BlackPink, Ikon, and Winner. ",
